Windstorms have destroyed about 220 houses and properties worth millions of naira in some communities of Jahun Local Government Area, Jigawa State. Jahun LG Chairman, Ado Mai Unguwa, confirmed the incident to DAILY POST on Wednesday. The affected areas included; Kale, Kargo and Buraburi. He, however, sympathized with the victims of the disaster and promised to support the affected families. A resident told DAILY POST that the incident occurred on Tuesday night, rendering hundreds of families homeless. He said the windstorms blew off the roofs of some houses and some public buildings in the area. He, therefore, urged the state and government to support the victims.